<h1>Tailwind</h1>

<p>
    Nxt apps can use Tailwind v4 with zero Node. The pattern: drop the standalone Tailwind
    CLI binary in <code>tools/</code>, point an MSBuild target at it, link the compiled CSS
    from your layout. Done.
</p>

<h2>1. Install the standalone CLI</h2>
<p>
    The repo ships <code>./install-tailwind</code> — a one-shot bash script that downloads
    the right binary for your platform (Linux x64/arm64, macOS x64/arm64) to
    <code>./tools/tailwindcss</code>:
</p>

<pre><code>./install-tailwind                # latest v4
./install-tailwind v4.3.0         # pin a specific version</code></pre>

<p>The binary is gitignored — each developer runs the script once after cloning.</p>

<h2>2. Source CSS</h2>
<p>
    Tailwind v4 is CSS-first — no <code>tailwind.config.js</code>. Define
    <code>@@source</code> roots and a <code>@@theme</code> block in a single CSS file:
</p>

<pre><code>/* Styles/site.css */
@@import "tailwindcss";

@@source "../Pages/**/*.razor";
@@source "../Pages/**/*.cshtml";

@@theme &#123;
    --color-brand-50:  #eff6ff;
    --color-brand-500: #3b82f6;
    --color-brand-600: #2563eb;
    --color-brand-700: #1d4ed8;
&#125;</code></pre>

<h2>3. MSBuild target</h2>
<p>
    Drop this into your csproj. It runs the CLI before every C# compile, so
    <code>wwwroot/site.css</code> is always fresh and gets shipped via
    <code>MapStaticAssets</code>. If the binary isn't installed, you get a warning instead
    of a failure (existing CSS still serves):
</p>

<pre><code>&lt;PropertyGroup&gt;
  &lt;TailwindCli Condition="'$(TailwindCli)' == '' and Exists('$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\..\tools\tailwindcss')"&gt;$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\..\tools\tailwindcss&lt;/TailwindCli&gt;
  &lt;TailwindCli Condition="'$(TailwindCli)' == '' and Exists('$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\..\tools\tailwindcss.exe')"&gt;$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\..\tools\tailwindcss.exe&lt;/TailwindCli&gt;
&lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;

&lt;Target Name="BuildTailwind"
        BeforeTargets="BeforeBuild"
        Inputs="Styles/site.css;Pages/**/*.razor"
        Outputs="wwwroot/site.css"&gt;
  &lt;Warning Text="Tailwind CLI not found. Run ./install-tailwind from repo root."
           Condition="'$(TailwindCli)' == ''" /&gt;
  &lt;Exec Command='"$(TailwindCli)" --input Styles/site.css --output wwwroot/site.css --minify'
        Condition="'$(TailwindCli)' != ''"
        WorkingDirectory="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)" /&gt;
&lt;/Target&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>4. Link from your layout</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/site.css" /&gt;</code></pre>

<p>
    Tailwind tree-shakes — only the utilities you actually reference in a
    <code>.razor</code> end up in the output. A typical small app's
    <code>wwwroot/site.css</code> is 15–25&#160;KB minified.
</p>

<h2>Hot reload during dev</h2>
<p>
    In one terminal, run the CLI in watch mode; in another, <code>dotnet watch</code> or
    <code>./dev-sample</code>:
</p>

<pre><code>./tools/tailwindcss \
    -i samples/MyApp/Styles/site.css \
    -o samples/MyApp/wwwroot/site.css \
    --watch</code></pre>

